{
  "stem": "7414.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they divided each apartment on so many parts, as many entrances there were.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they left us only to-- the smallest two rooms with a kitchen, which you can approach only from the back yard.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one night, [PAUSES] I think it was [PAUSES] around [PAUSES] March or February.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was still very cold.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They came at night, [PAUSES] and we knew that they are rounding up people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They're rounding up, again, richer people, and especially those who came from the other side, you know, because the Jews started to flee from the German side.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they stopped in Przemysl, because it was quite [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they had to register.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they were rounding up those what they called [NON-ENGLISH], that was the-- who fled.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES] so when they started to, to, to arrest, always in the middle of the night, when they arrested the richer, nationalized people, [? this, ?] my father was ready.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were sitting.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when we heard at night those heavy boots on the staircase, we were sitting there ready.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But they missed us, [PAUSES] and they went up.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then the janitor's wife came crying that they came for Rosa.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was the wife of a political prisoner.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was the system in Russia, that they arrested all the families of the political prisoners.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On the second floor, above us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES] And they took, this night, I went-- so I went up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was always in the middle of everything, because I did not want my parents to send them, because they could gather the parents together with her, you know?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I went up to have a look what, if she needs a help, and she needed, because she was all alone with a three-month-old baby.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
